info.game_comments: 1991 College Championship final game 2. First 20 clues only.

(3, 1).clue: Under Charles IV this Czech capital became capital of the Holy Roman Empire

(5, 1).clue: One source says it's "lies agreed upon" & most agree that it "repeats itself"

(6, 1).clue: Some residents of Twin Peaks whoop it up at One-Eye Jack's, a den of inequity in this nearby country

(2, 2).clue: "You're in good hands with" this insurance company

(3, 2).clue: Like Rome, the oldest section of this Portuguese capital is built on seven hills

(6, 2).clue: "Presidential" name of the sheriff played by Michael Ontkean, we assume the buck stops in his office

(2, 3).clue: "Nothing outlasts" this Eveready battery, "They keep going and going and going"

(3, 3).clue: A Jamaican rail line connects this capital city with Montego Bay

(4, 3).clue: Because they have only 1 shell, sea snails aren't called bivalves but these

(6, 3).clue: She wrote in her "secret diary", "If only I could stop this fear of dreaming that I'm dying"

(3, 4).clue: The Universal Postal Union & the Int'l Copyright Union are both located in this Swiss capital

(4, 4).clue: Fairy shrimps have compound ones on stalks

(6, 4).clue: Menacing truck driver played by actor Aldo Ray's son Eric Da Re, or a sign of the zodiac

(3, 5).clue: A park & monument in this city honor Nicaraguan poet Ruben Dario

(4, 5).clue: This sea animal once believed to use 2 of its arms as sails, was named for the men who sailed with Jason

(6, 5).clue: His 1st line on the show was: "Diane. 11:30 a.m. February 24th. Entering the town of "Twin Peaks"
